TITLE: Adding Contextual Help to Compressed EUI Forms in React
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to add contextual help to compressed EUI forms using React and EUI components. It uses the `EuiToolTip` component to wrap the label of an EuiFormRow, providing an explanation of the control. It also shows how to use the `helpText` prop for validation help text. The example includes an EuiFieldText and EuiSelect component to showcase the use of tooltips and help text for different form controls.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/packages/website/docs/components/forms/layouts/compressed-forms.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import React from 'react';
import {
  EuiFieldText,
  EuiFormRow,
  EuiSelect,
  EuiPanel,
  EuiIcon,
  EuiToolTip,
} from '@elastic/eui';

export default () => (
  <EuiPanel style={{ maxWidth: 300 }}>
    <EuiFormRow
      label="Text field"
      helpText="Show validation help text only."
      display="columnCompressed"
    >
      <EuiFieldText name="first" compressed />
    </EuiFormRow>

    <EuiFormRow
      label={
        <EuiToolTip content="Otherwise use an EuiToolTip around the label of the form row.">
          <span>
            Label <EuiIcon type="questionInCircle" color="subdued" />
          </span>
        </EuiToolTip>
      }
      display="columnCompressed"
    >
      <EuiSelect
        options=[
          { value: 'option_one', text: 'Option one' },
          { value: 'option_two', text: 'Option two' },
          { value: 'option_three', text: 'Option three' },
        ]
        compressed
      />
    </EuiFormRow>
  </EuiPanel>
);
```

