TITLE: Styling with useEuiTheme and Emotion
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to use the `useEuiTheme` hook to access EUI's theme tokens and apply them using Emotion's `css` prop.  It retrieves theme values for colors and sizes and applies them to `EuiIcon` and `EuiText` components. Requires `@emotion/react`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/packages/website/docs/getting-started/setup.mdx#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import React from 'react';
import { EuiIcon, EuiCode, EuiText, useEuiTheme } from '@elastic/eui';
import { css } from '@emotion/react';

export default () => {
  const { euiTheme } = useEuiTheme();

  return (
    <EuiText>
      <p>
        <EuiIcon
          type="stopFilled"
          size="xxl"
          css={{ color: euiTheme.colors.primary }}
        />{' '}
        This primary color will adjust based on the light or dark theme value
      </p>

      <p
        css={css`
          background: ${euiTheme.colors.lightShade};
          padding: calc(${euiTheme.size.base} * 2);
        `}
      >
        The padding of this box is created using <EuiCode>calc()</EuiCode>{' '}
        because EUI&apos;s theme sizes are string pixel values that are
        calculated off the theme&apos;s <EuiCode>base</EuiCode>
      </p>
    </EuiText>
  );
};
```

