TITLE: Adding secondary link actions to EuiListGroup items using React
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to add secondary actions to `EuiListGroupItem` components using the `extraAction` prop.  Each list item has a star icon that toggles between filled and empty states when clicked, simulating a favorite action.  It uses the `useGeneratedHtmlId` hook to generate unique IDs for the list items and React's `useState` hook to manage the state of each favorite.  The code depends on `EuiListGroup`, `EuiListGroupItem`, and `useGeneratedHtmlId` components from the `@elastic/eui` library.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/packages/website/docs/components/display/list-group.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import {
  EuiListGroup,
  EuiListGroupItem,
  useGeneratedHtmlId,
} from '@elastic/eui';

export default () => {
  const [favorite1, setFavorite1] = useState<string | undefined>(undefined);
