TITLE: EuiFocusTrap Interactive Example (React/TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This interactive example demonstrates the usage of the EuiFocusTrap component. It initializes a state variable `isDisabled` to control whether the focus trap is enabled or disabled. The `toggleDisabled` function updates this state.  The EuiFocusTrap component wraps an EuiPanel containing a form (FormExample) and a button to toggle the focus trap.  An external button outside the trap demonstrates the focus trapping behavior. It relies on components from `@elastic/eui` like EuiBadge, EuiButton, EuiFocusTrap, EuiPanel, EuiSpacer, and EuiText.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/packages/website/docs/utilities/focus-trap/index.mdx#_snippet_0

