TITLE: Initializing Nested EuiContextMenu in React
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a nested context menu using EuiContextMenu within an EuiPopover. It defines a `panels` array to structure the menu hierarchy, including nested panels, buttons with onClick handlers, links, tooltips, and disabled options.  It uses React hooks like `useState` and `useGeneratedHtmlId` for managing the popover state and generating unique IDs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/packages/website/docs/components/navigation/context-menu.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import {
  EuiButton,
  EuiContextMenu,
  EuiFormRow,
  EuiIcon,
  EuiPopover,
  EuiSwitch,
  EuiSpacer,
  useGeneratedHtmlId,
} from '@elastic/eui';

export default () => {
  const [isPopoverOpen, setPopover] = useState(false);

  const embeddedCodeSwitchId__1 = useGeneratedHtmlId({
    prefix: 'embeddedCodeSwitch',
    suffix: 'first',
