TITLE: Implementing ColorPicker with Empty State and Clearable Option (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use the `placeholder` and `isClearable` props of the `EuiColorPicker` component to provide context for an "empty" color picker and allow users to easily remove color selection. It also utilizes the `useMemo` hook to determine if the component is invalid based on the color and errors state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/packages/website/docs/components/forms/other/color-picker.mdx#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import React, { useMemo } from 'react';
import { EuiColorPicker, EuiFormRow, useColorPickerState } from '@elastic/eui';

export default () => {
  const [color, setColor, errors] = useColorPickerState();
  const isInvalid = useMemo(() => color !== '' && !!errors, [color, errors]);

  return (
    <React.Fragment>
      <EuiFormRow label="Pick a color" isInvalid={isInvalid} error={errors}>
        <EuiColorPicker
          onChange={setColor}
          color={color}
          isInvalid={isInvalid}
          placeholder="Auto"
          isClearable={true}
        />
      </EuiFormRow>
    </React.Fragment>
  );
};
```

