TITLE: EuiButton Loading State
DESCRIPTION: This interactive example demonstrates how to display a loading state on an EuiButton. The `isLoading` prop toggles the loading spinner and disables the button. It also shows how to change the button text to indicate the loading status.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/packages/website/docs/components/navigation/buttons/button.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import React, { useState } from 'react';

import {
  EuiButton,
  EuiSpacer,
  EuiSwitch,
} from '@elastic/eui';

export default () => {
  const [loadingButton, setLoadingButton] = useState(true);

  return(
    <>
      <EuiSwitch
        compressed
        label="Is loading"
        checked={loadingButton}
        onChange={() => setLoadingButton(!loadingButton)}
      />
      <EuiSpacer />
      <EuiButton isLoading={loadingButton} fill>
        {loadingButton ? 'Loading...' : 'Button'}
      </EuiButton>
    </>
  );
};
```

