TITLE: Truncation Position Demo (EuiTextTruncate) - React/TSX
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the usage of the `truncationPosition` property for the `startEnd` truncation type.  It utilizes EuiFormRow and EuiFieldNumber to control the position. The EuiTextTruncate component is used to truncate the text based on the selected position.  It imports EuiPanel, EuiFormRow, EuiFieldNumber, EuiSpacer, EuiText, and EuiTextTruncate from '@elastic/eui'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/packages/website/docs/utilities/text-truncation.mdx#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import React, { useState } from 'react';

import {
  EuiPanel,
  EuiFormRow,
  EuiFieldNumber,
  EuiSpacer,
  EuiText,
  EuiTextTruncate,
} from '@elastic/eui';

export default () => {
  const [truncationPosition, setTruncationPosition] = useState(45);

  return (
    <EuiText>
      <EuiFormRow label="Truncation position">
        <EuiFieldNumber
          compressed
          value={truncationPosition}
          onChange={(e) => setTruncationPosition(Number(e.target.value))}
        />
      </EuiFormRow>
      <EuiSpacer />
      <EuiPanel css={{ inlineSize: '40ch', maxInlineSize: '100%' }}>
        <EuiTextTruncate
          text="But the dog wasn’t lazy, it was just practicing mindfulness, so it had a greater sense of life-satisfaction than that fox with all its silly jumping."
          truncation="startEnd"
          truncationPosition={truncationPosition}
        />
      </EuiPanel>
    </EuiText>
  );
};
```

