TITLE: Creating Basic EuiCard with Icon and Title (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to create a basic EuiCard component with an icon, title, and description. It uses EuiFlexGroup to display multiple cards in a row. The icons are dynamically generated from an array, and a card can be disabled based on the item name. An onClick handler is provided for each card, although it is currently empty.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/packages/website/docs/components/containers/card.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import React from 'react';
import { EuiCard, EuiIcon, EuiFlexGroup, EuiFlexItem } from '@elastic/eui';

const icons = ['Beats', 'Cloud', 'Kibana'];

const cardNodes = icons.map(function (item, index) {
  return (
    <EuiFlexItem key={index}>
      <EuiCard
        icon={<EuiIcon size="xxl" type={`logo${item}`} />}
        title={`Elastic ${item}`}
        isDisabled={item === 'Kibana' ? true : false}
        description="Example of a card's description. Stick to one or two sentences."
        onClick={() => {}}
      />
    </EuiFlexItem>
  );
});

export default () => <EuiFlexGroup gutterSize="l">{cardNodes}</EuiFlexGroup>;
```

