TITLE: Getting Column Footer Content React
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet determines the content of a column's footer based on the `column.footer` property. If it's null, it returns null; if it's a function, it executes the function with items and pagination data; otherwise, it returns the value of column.footer. If undefined, it returns undefined.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/packages/website/docs/components/tabular-content/tables/custom.mdx#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
getColumnFooter = (
    column: Column,
    {
      items,
      pagination,
    }: {
      items: DataItem[];
      pagination: Pagination;
    }
  ) => {
    if (column.footer === null) {
      return null;
    }

    if (column.footer) {
      if (typeof column.footer === 'function') {
        return column.footer({ items, pagination });
      }
      return column.footer;
    }

    return undefined;
  };
```

