DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates the incorrect use of non-semantic HTML elements and CSS classes to define page structure. It highlights the problem of using generic `<div>` and `<ul>` elements with class names to represent landmarks, which provides no semantic meaning to screen readers. The example illustrates anti-patterns in accessible HTML structure.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/packages/website/docs/getting-started/accessibility.mdx#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: HTML
CODE:
```
  <body>
