TITLE: Creating Color Mode Specific Components (JSX/TSX)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates the recommended pattern for creating components that are specific to a particular color mode within EUI. It involves creating an internal component (`_EuiComponentName`) that contains the actual functionality and styles, and a wrapper component (`EuiComponentName`) that renders the internal component within an `<EuiThemeProvider>` with the desired `colorMode`. This pattern ensures that the component always uses the specified color mode, regardless of the surrounding context.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/wiki/contributing-to-eui/developing/writing-styles-with-emotion.md#_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
const _EuiComponentName = ({ componentProps }) => {
  return <div />;
}

export const EuiComponentName = ({ componentProps }) => {
    const Component = _EuiComponentName;
    return (
      <EuiThemeProvider colorMode={ colorMode }>
        <Component {...componentProps} />
      </EuiThemeProvider>
    );
  }
);
```

