TITLE: Initializing EuiTourStep with Element Wrapping - React/TSX
DESCRIPTION: This snippet initializes and displays an `EuiTourStep` component by wrapping an existing element (`EuiFieldText`). The state `isOpen` controls the visibility of the tour step. The `content`, `isStepOpen`, `minWidth`, `onFinish`, `step`, `stepsTotal`, `title`, `subtitle`, `anchorPosition`, and `zIndex` props are used to customize the tour step's appearance and behavior.  It utilizes `EuiButtonEmpty` to trigger the tour and `EuiSpacer` for visual separation. It depends on React hooks for state management and EUI components for styling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/packages/website/docs/components/display/tour/index.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { EuiButtonEmpty, EuiFieldText, EuiText, EuiSpacer, EuiTourStep } from '@elastic/eui';

export default () => {
  const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);

  const beginTour = () => {
    setIsOpen(true);
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <EuiButtonEmpty size="s" flush="left" iconType="refresh" onClick={beginTour}>
        Begin tour
      </EuiButtonEmpty>
      <EuiSpacer size="m" />
      <EuiTourStep
        content={
          <EuiText>
            <p>The tour step content.</p>
          </EuiText>
        }
        isStepOpen={isOpen}
        minWidth={300}
        onFinish={() => setIsOpen(false)}
        step={1}
        stepsTotal={1}
        title="Title of the current step"
        subtitle="Title of the full tour (optional)"
        anchorPosition="rightCenter"
        zIndex={1}
      >
        <EuiFieldText
          placeholder="Placeholder text"
        />
      </EuiTourStep>
    </div>
  );
};
```

