TITLE: extractRouter HOC for react-router (v5.x)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create an `extractRouter` Higher-Order Component (HOC) to intercept the router instance in react-router 5.x and pass it to a custom handler. This is necessary because of changes in React Context handling in react-router 5.0.  The onRouter prop is a callback function that receives the router object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/wiki/consuming-eui/react-router.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
// extractRouter.hoc.js
import { withRouter } from 'react-router-dom';

export const extractRouter = onRouter => WrappedComponent =>
  withRouter(
    class extends Component {
      componentDidMount() {
        const { match, location, history } = this.props;
        const router = { route: { match, location }, history };
        onRouter(router);
      }

      render() {
        return <WrappedComponent {...this.props} />;
      }
    }
  );
```

