TITLE: Toggling All Items Selection in EuiTable
DESCRIPTION: This function toggles the selection state of all items in the table. It updates the state with a new `itemIdToSelectedMap` where all items are either selected or unselected based on the current selection state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/packages/website/docs/components/tabular-content/tables/custom.mdx#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
toggleAll = () => {
    const allSelected = this.areAllItemsSelected();
    const newItemIdToSelectedMap: State['itemIdToSelectedMap'] = {};
    this.items.forEach(
      (item) => (newItemIdToSelectedMap[item.id] = !allSelected)
