TITLE: Sharing react-router instance globally (v4.x)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to share the react-router instance globally in react-router 4.x by assigning it to a globally-available singleton within the app's root component. This makes the router available outside of React's context.  It differs slightly from v3 in the shape of the contextTypes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/eui/blob/main/wiki/consuming-eui/react-router.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { registerRouter } from './routing';

// App is your app's root component.
class App extends Component {
  static contextTypes = {
    router: PropTypes.shape({
      history: PropTypes.shape({
        push: PropTypes.func.isRequired,
        createHref: PropTypes.func.isRequired
      }).isRequired
    }).isRequired
  }

  constructor(...args) {
    super(...args);

    // Share the router with the app without requiring React or context.
    registerRouter(this.context.router);
  }
}

// <App> *must* be a child of <Router> because <App> depends on the context provided by <Router>
ReactDOM.render(
  <Router>
    <App />,
  </Router>,
  appRoot
)
```

